body:
Weekend Adventure

Pairing: Bucky x wife, Steve, Sam

Warning: Language

A/N: I love the shit-head side of Bucky and love writing about his domestic life along with the trouble he gets into. Hope you like it too.

“Thanks for the invite guys, I had a blast.” “It was no problem, we have to do it again soon” Nat said. I grabbed my bag from the trunk and waved as they drove off. I turned to walk in the house when I see my husband coming out of the garage, trying to be sneaky. What is he up to? “Hey honey! How was your weekend” I called out to him. He stopped dead in his tracks and slowly turned around. His gave me a big smile, “It was great! We went to a baseball game and then out to that pizza place we like. The kids are at the tower hanging out with Peter. He kept them overnight, so we all went out. How was your weekend?” I slowly walked up to him, dropped my bag, and put my arms around his neck. I pulled him down like I was going to kiss him, but looked him straight in the eyes, “It was a fun weekend at the spa, ya know. Had a lot of girl talk, the usual. What’s going on? You’re sneaking out of the garage like you’re hiding something.” About that time the door opens up. Steve and Sam come out arguing about upholstery cleaning. They look up to see me and stop. Steve looks down sheepishly and rubs the back of his neck while Sam just smiles. “Hi boys. What brings you to our neck of the woods today?” “We just got back from eating lunch and were about to head back. Buck drove so he’s gonna give us a ride back.” I could see my him shaking his head vigorously out of the corner of my eye. “Ok, well you can grab the kids while you’re there. I’m just gonna go to the store and pick some stuff up for dinner.”

I left them and went inside to drop my bag off and get the grocery list. I went back out to see them huddled up. “Hey doll, why don’t we just all head to the tower and eat dinner there?” “I think everyone has had enough take-out this weekend. I’m gonna cook a homemade dinner. Now, if you’ll get out of my way I need to get going.” I sidestepped him and opened the overhead door. When I turned to get in the van I stopped. It was beat to hell. I slowly walked up to it and opened a back door. It was trashed. There were wrappers everywhere along with cans. There was silly string all over the roof and someone had written in marker all over my seats, like graffiti. I could hear him now. “I know it’s looks bad, but I’ll get it cleaned up and fixed. We got a little out of hand. I’m sorry.” I took a deep breath and looked at the 3 of them. “You bet your asses you will. I’m sure it wasn’t just James that made the mess. I want it spotless and looking new by the end of the week. And you’re driving it today while you go get the groceries and the kids. Got it?” He looked like a little kid getting scolded, “Yes dear, I got it.” I pointed to Sam & Steve, “And you 2 are going with him while he runs said errands.” They agreed. I was walking away when I heard one of them say something about bullet holes. I whipped around. “What in the fresh hell did you do to get shot at?!”

“Well ya see, we were heading home from the bar and we noticed we were being followed. Don’t worry, we had Happy be DD. Anyways, he did the usual 4 left turns and sure enough they followed us. I happened to remember hiding some firearms in the van so we proceeded to try and lose them. Needless to say they hit your van a couple of times before we shot their tires out. Didn’t cause too much of a disturbance.” I sighed and pinched the bridge of my nose. These were the only men on the planet that attracted trouble more than a toddler left unsupervised. “You know what, I’m getting a new vehicle. As a matter of fact I now claim your truck as mine. You can drive the damn van for the foreseeable future. I plan on getting a new one, but when I am damn good and ready to. Got it?! Now, you guys best get going. And you’re cooking dinner.” I handed him the list and went inside to take a hot bath. Bucky turned to his friends, “Come on, we better get going. I just hope Tony doesn’t see me driving this, I’ll never live it down.”


@loricameback

title: Spitting Out Seeds
body:
7k. WIP. Frostmaster. Dub con. 

My Ao3 | Send requests | Tip jar!

When Loki falls from the Bifrost, he lands hard upon the planet that will soon be named as Sakaar. He meets a curious stranger named the Grandmaster, and feels off-balance with him from the start.

                                              Read on Ao3 here!

Excerpt:

“What would you do if I did refuse?”  He doesn’t know why he asks, perhaps because he is a fool, but he tries to wrench himself free and he finds he cannot beneath the impossible strength of the Grandmaster’s clutching hands, the slight smirk of his lips.

“Take, uh, take what I wanted,” the Grandmaster murmurs, lowering his mouth to the side of Loki’s knee and pressing a kiss through the silken fabric. Loki sits back on his heels, staring down at the other man as his mouth slowly hovers over the inner part of Loki’s thigh, coming lower, lower—

“You wouldn’t,” Loki whispers. Fear is hot beneath his skin.

“Oh, I would,” the Grandmaster replies. His mouth is so close now, so close to Loki’s cock, to the two openings between his legs, and why, why should this electrify his skin, cause his very magic to bubble to the surface? Why should a being of such clear power threatening rape affect him to such obscene arousal? He can feel himself hardening some as his skin grows more sensitive, as he feels the Grandmaster’s fingers play upon the lines of his thighs, as he feels his hot breath.
